 Est Media Vagyonkezelo Nyrt., a
Hungarian entertainment company, fell for a second day after
saying yesterday that it will  issue bonds  to help refinance
debt.  The shares dropped 7.3 percent to 101 forint by 10:06 a.m.
in Budapest after a 4.4 percent decline yesterday. The stock
reached a record low of 90 forint on April 11.  To contact the reporter on this story:
